text: Emergency team performed an urgent tracheostomy on the 7-year-old patient who was experiencing severe कफ़ and extreme difficulty breathing after being diagnosed with severe पैब्लोइड डिस्प्लाज़िया.
The patient was rushed to the ICU after experiencing severe chest pain, shortness of breath, and a sudden drop in blood pressure due to a cardiac arrest caused by a severe case of हृदय रोग.
55-year-old male patient, having a history of Asthma, was rushed to the ER due to severe Chest pain and shortness of breath after consuming a small amount of peanut.
A 30-year-old woman with a history of गंभीर चिंता and hypertension underwent an emergency 心脏手术 after experiencing severe ब्रेडिकार्डिया.
The patient was admitted to the ICU due to सीने में दर्द (chest pain) after an angioplasty procedure, which revealed severe ट्यूमर (tumor) growth.

The 35-year-old patient developed severe shortness of breath and chest tightness after undergoing an urgent angioplasty procedure for acute myocardial infarction (-heart attack) and was administered 0.5mg Atropine.
The emergency room doctor ordered an immediate blood transfusion for the patient suffering from severe ब्लड शुगर and थायराइड failure, who had experienced sudden chest pain and तेज़ सिर दर्द.

Emergency team rushed the patient with acute pancreatitis to the ICU where he was administered 1g of cefotaxime and placed on a ventilator after showing severe respiratory distress and severe abdominal pain.
The doctor ordered an emergency कार्डियोपल्मोनरी आरेस्ट (CPR) procedure for the patient showing symptoms of severe स्ट्रोक (stroke) after a blood test revealed high levels of Troponin.

The cardiologist performed urgent pacemaker implantation (Biventricular ICD) to treat the patient's severe heart failure (NYHA Class III) with recent onset of shortness of breath and peripheral edema.
The 65-year-old patient with severe ब्रेन हेमorrhage was immediately rushed to the emergency OT for an urgent डायलिसिस procedure.
The patient with severe किडनी फेल (kidney failure) developed हृदय रोग (heart disease) after undergoing bypass surgery and was prescribed 100mg Aspirin twice daily.
The doctor ordered a chest X-ray for the patient showing symptoms of possible تेज़ बुखार, severe Chest pain, and shortness of breath after administering 0.5mg of Morphine.
Patient को emergency appendectomy के बाद 24 hours के लिए low-dose IV antibiotics दिए गए थे क्योंकि उसे severe पेट दर्द और तेज़ बुखार था।

Patient ko तेज़ बुखार और सांस लेने में दिक्कत के कारण डॉक्टर ने इंटेंसिव केयर यूनिट में भर्ती कराया जिसने बाद में Angioplasty की सलाह दी गई जिसके बाद हृदय की मांसपेशियों में कमजोरी के कारण नायज़ी पैंसुलर इन्सुलिन की 10 IU खुराक दी गई।
The emergency room doctor performed an emergency angioplasty procedure on Sunday morning after the patient experienced severe chest pain and high blood pressure.
Emergency room doctors performed an urgent Cardiac Catheterization procedure on a patient with severe chest pain and high fever of 103°C after a few minutes of severe palpitations.

डॉक्टर ने मरीज़ को अस्पताल में भर्ती करने की सिफारिश की क्योंकि उसे सांस फूलने और तेज़ बुखार के साथ तीव्र संक्रमण था। जांच में पता चला कि मरीज़ को दिल के दौरे का इतिहास है, और डॉक्टर ने निमसॉलिड (Nimsolid) और 0.5mg इवाबामेद (Ivabamid) नामक मधुमेह के लिए दवाएं लिख दीं।
एक 35 वर्षीय महिला को दिल के दौरे से पहले Angioplasty की सलाह दी गई थी, जिसमें Cardiac Catheterization और Cardiac MRI टेस्ट की जांच की गई थी।
The emergency room doctor ordered an urgent X-ray and administered 1mg/kg Morphine for the patient experiencing severe chest pain and तेज़ बुखार.
उसे Cardiac Arrest के बाद कार्डियोसर्जन ने Angioplasty के बाद Oxygen सपोर्ट के साथ ही ICU में भर्ती किया।
Emergency was triggered as the patient with severe दिल का दौरा से मृत्यु had an Allergen reaction to Penicillin during Angioplasty procedure and required immediate blood transfusion.
कैंसर के शुरुआती चरण में इलाज के लिए पेशेंटर को कीमोथेरेपी और लेजर थेरेपी का प्रशासन किया गया था, जो कैंसर के कारण अन्य स्थितियों जैसे अनिद्रा को दूर करने की संभावना को मिलाया जाता है।

The patient with severe टीबी (TB) was undergoing an emergency कार्डियोरेसुसिशयाटन (cardiorenal transplantation) procedure after developing cardiac arrest and severe हृदय रोग (heart disease) symptoms, including तेज़ बुखार (high fever) and सांस की तकलीफ (shortness of breath), which triggered a स्पाइनल टेप (spinal tap) and electroencephalogram (EEG) tests.
The patient with स्ट्रोक के लक्षण was immediately taken to the ER for an emergency angioplasty after showing severe वेंट्रिकल फाईब्रिलेशन on the ECG.
Dr. जोशी ने किडनी का फेल होने के बाद ट्रांसप्लांट सर्जरी (Transplant Surgery) की सलाह दी जहाँ मरीज़ को एंटीबायोटिक्स (Ceftriaxone) और immunosuppression दवाएं दी गईं।

The patient was immediately rushed to the ICU after experiencing severe chest pain and shortness of breath, which led to a diagnosis of acute myocardial infarction, and was administered 300mg Aspirin and 150mg Metoprolol.
Patient ko तेज़ बुखार और सीने में दर्द के लिए डॉक्टर ने कोरोनरी एंजियोग्राफी की सलाह दी और हेपरिन नामक दवा देने का निर्देश दिया।
The doctor ordered an emergency Angioplasty procedure for the patient with a severe heart attack (हृदयाघात) after an abnormal ECG report and high potassium levels.

The patient with हृदय रोग was rushed to the emergency room after complaining of chest pain, shortness of breath, and severe सिरदर्द. The doctor immediately ordered an ECG, blood test, and CT scan to diagnose the underlying condition, which was later confirmed as a blood clot in the coronary artery. The patient was immediately administered 150mg of Warfarin and was advised to take 81mg of Aspirin twice daily.

During the cardiac arrest, doctors administered 200mg Adrenaline through an ICD implant after detecting elevated Troponin T levels, and also administered oxygen through a face mask due to severe respiratory distress.

The doctor ordered an ECG and blood test for the patient with severe chest pain and high fever after a car accident, and prescribed 4mg Morphine for pain relief and 125mg Aspirin for antiplatelet therapy.
Doctor ने patient को immediate blood transfusion के लिए कहा क्योंकि वे severe Chest pain और तेज़ बुखार से पीड़ित हैं।
Emergency teams were dispatched to the hospital for a patient experiencing severe tेज़ बुखार and chest pain after an angioplasty procedure.
The patient को severe pneumonia के लिए बेहतर इलाज के लिए जांच के बाद ECMO हस्तक्षेप की आवश्यकता थी, जिसके लिए 80mg Atorvastatin लेने की सलाह दी गई थी।

A 35-year-old woman underwent emergency surgery for Acute Appendicitis and was administered 3 units of blood due to severe internal bleeding and was monitored with continuous Endoscopic Ultrasound (EUS) and CT Scan.
The 30-year-old patient with diagnosed किडनी फेल्योर underwent emergency डायलिसिस and was prescribed 2mg Lisinopril for साइनसिटिस.

Emergency team performed cardiac arrest algorithm after 3-minute bystander CPR, which included administering 1mg Epinephrine IV and defibrillation following an abnormal ECG and severe हृदय रोग के लक्षण.
The patient के लिए emergency के समय एंबुलेंस से अस्पताल ले जाया गया, जहां डॉक्टर ने फेफड़ों में खराबी (COPD) का पता लगाया और बायपास सर्जरी की सिफारिश की, जिसमें कॉरोनरी आर्टरी ग्राफ्टिंग शामिल थी।
The patient को कोरोना वायरस संक्रमण के लक्षणों के कारण ICU में भर्ती किया गया था और उन्हें एंटीवायरल दवा Oseltamivir 75mg दिन में दो बार दी गई।

The doctor performed an emergency cardiac bypass surgery on the patient with a severe blockage in the coronary artery, after the patient's Electrocardiogram (ECG) report showed arrhythmia and abnormal heart rate, and the patient was having severe chest pain, सीने का दर्द, and shortness of breath, श्वास की कमी।
मरीज़ ने एक गंभीर दिल का दौरा पड़ने के बाद अस्पताल में भर्ती हो गई और उसी दिन दिल के दौरे के संभावित कारणों को निर्मूल करने के लिए एक कैथेटरीकल एब्लेशन बायपास सर्जरी कराई गई।
The patient was experiencing severe Chest pain and shortness of breath, thus underwent immediate Angioplasty under general anesthesia.

The patient presented with severe chest pain, shortness of breath, and high fever of 103°F. Emergency physicians performed an ECG and blood work (Lipid Profile) to identify heart attack risk. Doctors also inquired about dust allergy (धूल allergy) to manage respiratory issues.
Doctor ने मरीज़ को तुरंत Angioplasty सर्जरी से जोड़ें क्योंकि उनके दिल में एक बड़ा दिल का दौरा पड़ा था जिसके चलते Cardiac arrest हुआ।
After a cardiac arrest, the emergency team performed CPR on the patient for 20 minutes before transporting him to the ICU for an angioplasty surgery to clear the blocked coronary artery.
The patient with acute खाँसी and सीने में दर्द underwent an emergency CT scan and was administered 2mg Morphine for severe फेफड़ों का संक्रमण.
The 45-year-old patient presented with severe chest pain and shortness of breath after sudden cardiac arrest, so she was administered 200mg of Aspirin while undergoing cardiac catheterization.

The patient was immediately taken to the ICU for emergency surgery due to severe cardiac arrest and was administered 2mg Atropine IV followed by an ECG and blood gas analysis to manage the anaphylaxis caused by a Penicillin allergy.

The emergency department doctor performed an urgent C-Section after the patient's pregnancy was complicated by severe hypertension and multiple seizures - high blood pressure of 220/150 mmHg causing severe headache and blurred vision - and she had an allergy to Penicillin.
एक तेज़ बुखार और सीने के दर्द के कारण, डॉक्टर ने मरीज़ को एंटीबायोटिक्स कोर्स और एक सांस लेने की कोशिश करने के लिए अस्पताल में भर्ती कराया।

The 30-year-old patient was rushed to the emergency room with severe allergic reaction after taking Penicillin, suffering from तेज़ बुखार and chest pain, and underwent an immediate एंटीबायोटिक treatment.
